{{Infobox institute |name = International Institute for Hermeneutics |image = |image_size = |image_alt = |caption = |latin_name = |motto = |founder = |established = 2001 |mission = fostering a general [[hermeneutics]] |focus = |president = [[Andrzej Wiercinski]] |chairman = |head_label = |head = |faculty = |adjunct_faculty = |staff = |key_people = |budget = |endowment = |debt = |num_members = |subsidiaries = |owner = |non-profit_slogan = |former_name = |location = |coor = |address = |website = [http://www.iihermeneutics.org/ iihermeneutics.org] |footnotes = }}
'''International Institute for Hermeneutics (IIH)''' is an organization whose purpose is to foster and articulate a general [[hermeneutics]], a task demanding an intensive [[interdisciplinary]] collaboration on a level that does not yet exist in the contemporary university.<ref>{{cite web|title=Welcome to the International Institute for Hermeneutics|url=http://www.iihermeneutics.org/president-s-welcome|website=International Institute for Hermeneutics|accessdate=16 October 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=International Institute for Hermeneutics {{!}} Yearbook Profile {{!}} Union of International Associations|url=https://www.uia.org/s/or/en/1122278495|website=[[Union of International Associations]]|accessdate=16 October 2017|language=en}}</ref> [[Andrzej Wiercinski]] is president and founder of the International Institute for Hermeneutics. The Institute publishes [[Analecta Hermeneutica]] and [[International Studies in Hermeneutics and Phenomenology]].
