[[Image:Vorilong - Super quattuor libros Sententiarum Petri Lombardi, 1489 - 4419144.tif|thumb|''Super quattuor libros Sententiarum Petri Lombardi'', 1489]]
'''William Vorilong''', also known as '''Guillermus Vorrilong''', '''Willem of Verolon''', '''William of Vaurouillon''', '''Guilelmus de Valle Rouillonis''', etc.[http://thesaurus.cerl.org/record/cnp00927983] (ca. 1390 - 1463)<ref>[http://www.daviddarling.info/encyclopedia/V/Vorilong.html Vorilong] at the Encyclopedia of Science</ref> was a French [[philosopher]] and [[theologian]].<ref>{{cite book|last1=Eisen|first1=Arri |last2=Laderman|first2=Gary|title=Science, religion, and society: an encyclopedia of history, culture, and controversy, Volume 1|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=eOUpAQAAMAAJ&q=vorilong&dq=vorilong&hl=en&sa=X&ei=e4rkUJuPIKmw0QWu9IDQCw&ved=0CEoQ6AEwBTgU|year=2007|publisher=M E Sharpe|page=298}}</ref> He wrote a biography of [[Duns Scotus]]. From 1457 onwards he was a [[regent master]] in Lyon, becoming licentiate and master of theology at Lyon in 1458.

